Hi,

I'm using esbuild to convert my esm modules to cjs so I can have a hybrid library that support both import and require.

My esbuild is:
```js
esbuild.build({
  entryPoints,
  bundle: false,
  platform: 'node',
  format: 'cjs',
  outdir: `${pkg}/dist/cjs/`,
}).catch((err) => {
  process.exit(1);
});
```

My javascript:
```js
// ./test1.js
export default class Test1 {}

// ./test2.js
import Test1 from './test1.js';
class Test2 extends Test1 {}
```

The built`./test1.js` seems correct `{ default: [Getter] }`
However, in `./test2.js` it's wrapped as `__toESM(require("./test1.js"), 1);` so it becomes `{ default: { default: [Getter] } }`

Because of that, if you import the built file using `require('./test2.js')` you  get `Uncaught TypeError: Class extends value #<Object> is not a constructor or null`.

Did I miss anything?

